Package com.thomsonreuters.upa.examples.common

This package provides functionality shared by examples.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ReceivedMsgCallback
    Callback method used by ProviderSession.read(Channel, com.thomsonreuters.upa.transport.Error, ReceivedMsgCallback) to process client request.
    ResponseCallback
    Callback used for processing a response message.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ChannelSession
    Manages UPA channel and provides methods for connection establishment, channel initialization, read, and write methods for Consumer and NIProvider example applications.
    ClientSessionInfo
    Client session information.
    CommandLine
    Used by examples to assist in processing command line arguments.
    DirectoryHandler
    This is the source directory handler for the UPA consumer application.
    DirectoryRequestInfo
    Source directory request information.
    DirectoryRequestInfoList
    Source directory request information list.
    GenericResponseStatusFlags
    Status flags used by the UPA Java Generic Consumer and Provider applications.
    LoginHandler
    This is the Login handler for the UPA Consumer and NIProvider application.
    LoginRequestInfo
    Login request information.
    LoginRequestInfoList
    Login request information list.
    PingHandler
    The ping handler for the example applications.
    ProviderDirectoryHandler
    This is the source directory handler for the UPA Java Provider application.
    ProviderLoginHandler
    This is the implementation of processing of login requests and login status messages.
    ProviderSession
    Encapsulate UPA transport methods for the interactive provider and generic provider example applications.
    UnSupportedMsgHandler
    This is the implementation of sending unsupported status message for the interactive provider and generic provider applications.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ConsumerLoginState
    Consumer login states.
    DirectoryRejectReason
    Reasons a directory request is rejected
    LoginRejectReason
    reasons a login request is rejected
